{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://digbmc.github.io/pta-manifests/phan/phan-02724/manifest.json","type":"Manifest","label":{"none":["PHAN-02724"]},"metadata":[{"label":{"none":["Timestamp"]},"value":{"none":["0:27:24"]}},{"label":{"none":["Film"]},"value":{"none":["Phantom Thread"]}},{"label":{"none":["Creator"]},"value":{"none":["Paul Thomas Anderson"]}},{"label":{"none":["Distance"]},"value":{"none":["plan américain"]}},{"label":{"none":["Angle"]},"value":{"none":["low"]}},{"label":{"none":["Location"]},"value":{"none":["interior"]}},{"label":{"none":["Movement"]},"value":{"none":["fixed"]}},{"label":{"none":["Composition"]},"value":{"none":["two shot"]}}],"summary":{"none":["Two women shake hands."]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02724/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"homepage":[{"id":"PHAN-02724","type":"Text","format":"text/html","label":{"none":["Object homepage"]}}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02724/canvas/1","type":"Canvas","height":1080,"width":1920,"label":{"none":["PHAN-02724"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02724/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02724/canvas/1/annopage-1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02724/canvas/1/annopage-1/anno-1","type":"Annotation","motivation":"painting","target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02724/canvas/1","body":{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02724/tiles/full/1920,1080/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":1080,"width":1920,"service":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02724/tiles","type":"ImageService3","profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02724/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02724/canvas/1/b562b505-2a6a-4407-83f1-d043a72aa370","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-29T15:23:21.522Z","creator":"g","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p><em>Phantom Thread</em> begs for a Freudian reading, which some commentators have been all too willing to provide. From the way Reynolds adores the memory of his mother and has taken up her sewing craft to his desire for a stern mother figure, the dressmaker adheres closely to the Oedipal model. Cyril has stood in as a mother figure to provide the support that Reynolds demands to function on a basic level as well as to produce his art. The result, in Sophie Durbin’s view, is “an arrangement that very nearly violates” Freud’s “incest dread” (Durbin, “<a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" class=\"Hyperlink SCXW142265066 BCX4\" href=\"https://www.perisphere.org/2025/03/14/psychoanalyze-me-mommy-making-sense-of-the-mother-role-in-phantom-thread/\"><u>Psychoanalyze Me, Mommy</u></a>”).&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02724/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:85.2185608607935,68.06993947545399,475.15803631472767,256.94687289845325"}}}]}]}]}